  "texts": [
    "Plagiarism is another expression of academic misconduct that surfaced in the fifteenth century with the emergence of the printing press (Eaton 2021).",
    "It became more pronounced with the availability of vast online written material collections and editing (copy-paste) features in word-processing tools.",
    "Students resort to copying intellectual work from sources to complete written assignments without observing proper paraphrasing and attribution to the original authors (Bretag & Mahmud 2009).",
    "Because large language models generate text using training data from various existing digital resources, attributing original authorship becomes a complicated issue.",
    "This idea adds a layer of complexity in determining whether or not the written text generated or influenced by AI can be considered plagiarized."
  ],
